div.div:
API
Upload video: POST /video (chunked)Â
Watch video: GET /video/:videoId
Like Video: POST /video/:videoId/like
Post Comment: POST /video/:videoId/comment
Get Comment: GET /video/:videoId/comment/:commentId
Search for Video: GET /search?=""
Log in: POST /login
Sign up: POST /signup
Get user: GET /user/:userId

div.div:
Notes
- Shard videos by hash(id)
- Use KGS to pre-generate keys, store in db
- May want load balancing layer, could use API gateway to accomplish LB
- Use NoSQL for scale, maybe Cassandra
- Uploads are chunked and streamed
- Batch numViews updates in cache for X minutes before writing to DB, OK to lose some views
- Let video upload complete before responding to client, adding entry to DB,
ensure video was uploaded successfully
